(cognitive test, COG) (brain atrophy, %) COG

  1. COG

\[\begin{equation} \label{eq:1} S = \sqrt{\frac{(n_A - 1)S^2_A + (n_B - 1)S^2_B}{n_A + n_B -2}} \end{equation}\]

  • \(S_A:\) A
  • \(n_A:\) A
  • \(S_B:\) B
  • \(n_B:\) B
  • \(S:\) AB
  • \(n_A + n_B -2:\)

EZR t (degree of freedom) P 

2*pt(t value, degree of freedom, lower=FALSE)

9.0 Student t

\[ T = \frac{\bar{X}_A - \bar{X}_B}{S\sqrt{1/n_A + 1/n_B}} \]

()/ \[ \begin{aligned} \because\;\; S & = \sqrt{\frac{(n_A - 1)S^2_A + (n_B - 1)S^2_B}{n_A + n_B -2}} \\ \therefore\;\; S & = \sqrt{\frac{(50 - 1)9^2 + (150 - 1)9^2}{50 + 150 -2}} = 9 \\ \Rightarrow\;\; T & = \frac{\bar{X}_A - \bar{X}_B}{S\sqrt{1/n_A + 1/n_B}} \\ & = \frac{69.2 - 60.2}{9\times\sqrt{1/50 + 1/150}} \\ & = \frac{9}{9\times0.1633} = 6.1237 \end{aligned} \]

(degree of freedom) \(n_A + n_B -2 = 198\)P EZR 

2*pt(6.1237, 198, lower=FALSE)

  1. 2. (df)

\[\begin{equation} \label{eq:2} \mathbf{df} = \frac{(S^2_A/n_A + S^2_B/n_B)^2}{(S_A^2/n_A)^2/(n_A-1)+(S_B^2/n_B)^2/(n_B-1)} \end{equation}\]

EZR t (df) P 

2*pt(t value, df, lower=FALSE)

2.Welch t

\[ \begin{aligned} \Rightarrow\;\; T & = \frac{\bar{X}_A - \bar{X}_B}{\sqrt{S^2_A/n_A + S^2_B/n_B}} \\ & = \frac{0.67 - 0.23}{\sqrt{0.21^2/50 + 0.10^2/150}} \\ & = \frac{0.44}{\sqrt{0.0009486667}} = 14.28551 \end{aligned} \]

()

()\(\bar{X}\) \(X\)

  • variance:

\[ \begin{aligned} \mathbf{Var}(X) & = \frac{(X_1-\bar{X})^2+(X_2-\bar{X})^2+\cdots+(X_n-\bar{X})^2}{n - 1} \\ & = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(X_i-\bar{X})^2}{n -1} \end{aligned} \]

  • covariance:

\[ \begin{aligned} \mathbf{Cov}(X, Y) & = \frac{(X_1 - \bar{X})(Y_1-\bar{Y}) + (X_2 - \bar{X})(Y_2-\bar{Y}) + \cdots + (X_n - \bar{X})(Y_n-\bar{Y})}{n - 1} \\ & = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^n(X_i - \bar{X})(Y_i-\bar{Y})}{n - 1} \end{aligned} \]
